bonfyre-transcribe — world-class libwhisper transcription engine

Usage:
  bonfyre-transcribe <input-audio> <output-dir> [--model NAME] [--language CODE|auto]
                      [--media-prep-binary PATH]
                      [--silero-vad] [--silero-script PATH]
                      [--split-speech] [--noise-threshold DB] [--min-silence SEC]
                      [--min-speech SEC] [--padding SEC]
                      [--greedy] [--beam-size N] [--best-of N]
                      [--vocab-db PATH] [--no-vocab]
                      [--processors N] [--no-speech-thold N]

Transcription engine:
  Links libwhisper directly. Model loads ONCE. Zero fork+exec.
  Metal GPU + flash attention. DTW forced-alignment timestamps.
  Multi-processor parallel decode. TinyDiarize speaker turns.

Quality (cutting-edge):
  Geometric mean confidence (perplexity^-1 = exp(mean(log(p)))).
  Compression ratio hallucination detection (zlib, rho > 2.4).
  Token n-gram repetition detector. Repetition penalty logits filter.
  Voice-length anomaly detection. Per-segment quality score.

Output formats:
  transcript.txt   — plain text
  transcript.json  — structured segments with timestamps, confidence,
                     logprob, compression ratio, hallucination flags
  transcript.srt   — SubRip subtitles
  transcript.vtt   — WebVTT subtitles with quality metadata

Vocabulary learning:
  Flat binary .bfvocab format (BFVD02). Zero SQLite, zero process spawns.
  BM25-weighted terms injected as whisper initial_prompt.
  Token-aware truncation to fit decoder context (112 token budget).
  Shannon entropy + KL-divergence track convergence.

  BM25(t,d) = IDF(t) * tf(t,d)*(k1+1) / (tf(t,d)+k1*(1-b+b*|d|/avgdl))
  H = -sum(p_i * log2(p_i))           [Shannon entropy]
  D_KL(P||U) = sum(p_i * log2(p_i/q)) [KL from uniform]

  Disable with --no-vocab. Custom path with --vocab-db.
